    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) that serves as a benchmark for naturally aspirated performance. This example features the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure dual-VANOS system for razor-sharp throttle response. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M-differential lock. The chassis is in flawless condition, featuring factory-spec subframe reinforcement and refreshed bushings to maintain original kinematic precision. The exterior retains its factory depth with no signs of clear coat failure or panel gap deviation. Mechanically, the rod bearings and VANOS hub have been proactively addressed, with a comprehensive dossier of service records available. This is a turn-key collector piece for the discerning purist.",
